Requires BioFormats. Please note that OMERO plugins must be disabled in Fiji.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4lh4l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ola5","text":"As requirements, to use MethodsJ2, users first need a raw image from a microscopy experiment as well as a previously generated in Micro-Meta App microscope hardware specifications file (.json) (see bioRxiv preprint here).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":215,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":130,"length":14},{"key":2,"offset":215,"length":4}],"data":{}},{"key":"6521g","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b4h65","text":"The script runs in Fiji, and an active internet connection is required. A demo microscope hardware specifications file (.json) and image are provided to test the script.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"80918FB3D1F311ECA5680A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://github.com/ABIF-McGill/MethodsJ2/blob/main/fiji.sc"}},"1":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"99494690D1F311ECA5680A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://github.com/WU-BIMAC/MicroMetaApp-Electron/releases/tag/1.2.2-b1-1"}},"2":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"B10B2C55D1F311ECA5680A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2021.05.31.446382v2"}}}}
description: {"blocks":[{"key":"3kd61","text":"MethodsJ2","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dvvh6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2s1ro","text":"Building on MethodsJ , MethodsJ2 helps users write a materials and methods text for microscopy experiments by sourcing experiment information from metadata, as well as information from a microscope hardware configuration file generated in Micro-Meta App. A draft experiment methods section text is generated which can then be revised and used in written manuscripts and reports, etc.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":12,"length":8}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":12,"length":8}],"data":{}},{"key":"7hmjv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bau2i","text":"See our preprint MethodsJ2: A Software Tool to Improve Microscopy Methods Reporting on bioRxiv","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":17,"length":66}],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":17,"length":66}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"8571D50FD1F211ECA5680A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://github.com/tp81/MethodsJ"}},"1":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"F99FF3A6D1F211ECA5680A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2021.06.23.449674v1"}}}}
disclaimer: {"blocks":[{"key":"1i7qq","text":"DISCLAIMER: As per MethodsJ, this is not meant to be applied blindly, but rather to be used as a starting point. Metadata is recorded by the microscope driving software, so at best it reflects the way the microscope's software was configured. In addition, this script uses the fantastic BioFormats library. It has been designed to extract as much information as possible from the image data, but formats change occasionally so don't be surprised if the text doesn't completely reflect what you expect. If you do find some discrepancy, check with your facility staff (if the microscope is part of an imaging facility) for help on the appropriate wording or to check the configuration, and then with the BioFormats community to see if the metadata was not read correctly. If you believe there is an error in the script (not unlikely), feel free to reach out.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bliag","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1fdj1","text":"Importantly, please verify the text generation output and the csv file carefully or with someone familiar with the microscope or your experiments, in order to make sure that the information is correct, and that the grammar and syntax are ok, before copy-pasting the text into your manuscript.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":11}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

Verifies microscope manufacturer from image metadata and microscope hardware configuration file, alerts user if these are different. Outputs and saves a csv file containing all detected information (from image metadata) and all user input information (either manually entered or selected from Micro-Meta App hardware configuration file), as well as image file path, Micro-Meta App hardware configuration file path, and generated methods text output, allowing to check for discrepancies and to store and share the information. --Many thanks to our reviewers for these helpful suggestions!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":12}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3dphg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4v3mn","text":"Installation","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":12}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a1iga","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b28ur","text":"No installation required. MethodsJ2 text generation based on user input and on a Micro-Meta App hardware file:  Images were acquired on a Axiovert 200M Compound Commercial-custom modified inverted microscope  (Zeiss) Images had a width of 1012 and a height of 1020 pixels, 1 planes (z), 3 channels, 1 timepoints,  with dimensional order XYCZT. Voxels had a lateral size of 0.14 um.  DAPI was excited with a X-Cite 120 LED light source (Excelitas) set to 30 % and wavelength  selection was carried out with a G 365 excitation filter (Zeiss), a FT 395 dichroic mirror  (Zeiss) and a BP 445/50 emission filter (Zeiss). Alternatively, click on File \u003e New \u003e Script... to open a script editor window, and then in that script editor, click on File \u003e Open, navigate to the appropriate folder and select MethodsJ2_v1_2_.py","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Instructions with demo image and hardware specifications file
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"etjkg","text":"Once the script is loaded, make sure the appropriate language is selected - click on Language, select Python.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Instructions with demo image and hardware specifications file
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1mpgu","text":"Click the \"Run\" button, and follow the dialog boxes, filling in the information as accurately as possible. More information on each dialog box is given below","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Instructions with demo image and hardware specifications file
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1r865","text":"When first running the script in Fiji, it may take up to ~30 seconds for the script to launch (before seeing the first dialog box). Running the script is pretty quick, and simply depends on availability of the required information about the image. If all parameters are known by the user, it should take only a couple of minutes to go through the script and generate a draft methods section.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6nsjt","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"f71ip","text":"This first window will prompt you for a microscopy image file, in order to extract metadata. You can drag and drop a file into the text input field, or click Browse, navigate to the appropriate folder, and select the appropriate image. We recommend loading the metadata and Bio-Formats metadata (check boxes), which will open metadata files which can help fill in crucial information. ***As a demo, please select 'BPAE_3color_30p-200ms_63xOil_003_diffExp_Int__.czi'","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"E93EF4E0D1F611ECA48311566BB060D8","height":336,"id":308755,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/png","original_name":"image.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jpsxbn3x7.jpg","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jpsvbn3x7.jpg","type":1,"webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jpswbn3x7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jpsubn3x7.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b6m2i","text":"Then, please select where to save the csv output for this run of MethodsJ2. The csv file can be saved in the same folder as the image, or you can choose another folder.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f62tp","text":"Please note that MethodsJ2 will open the image in Fiji (using Bio-Formats), and so memory limits might apply.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7efo7","text":"A csv file is generated containing all the information detected from the image metadata and all the user input information (both manually entered and selected from the Micro-Meta App configuration file). The csv is saved either in the same folder as the image file, or in a folder selected by the user (in the first welcome dialog box). This csv file can be used to check for accuracy of the user-input information (compared to the metadata), and is the record for this particular run of MethodsJ2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ffhfc","text":"In many cases, information is input differently in the image metadata compared to how it is stored in Micro-Meta App (and OMERO). For example, information about the objective might be stored in the image metadata as \"PlanApo 100x NA 1.4 (Zeiss)\" or \"Zeiss 100X Plan-Apo 1.4 N.A.\" or other permutations of the same information, depending on who set up the microscope. This makes text/string matching difficult. Thus, in the csv file, the user can directly compare and judge for themselves whether the information is accurate, by directly comparing the image metadata information with the user selection.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
